      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(dispatch): route durable reasoning payloads to Telegram",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nUnder `/reasoning on`, Telegram users were not receiving thinking messages from reasoning models. The thinking content was correctly generated by the model and archived in the session, but the shared dispatch path (`dispatch-from-config.ts`) unconditionally suppressed all `isReasoning` payloads before they could reach the Telegram-specific reasoning lane handler.\n\nThis PR routes durable `isReasoning` block and final payloads through to Telegram by skipping the generic suppression when the delivery channel is Telegram. Other channels (WhatsApp, web, etc.) continue to suppress reasoning payloads as before.\n\nFixes #94937\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Telegram `/reasoning on` durable thinking delivery — ensures `isReasoning` block and final payloads are allowed through for Telegram while remaining suppressed for non-Telegram channels.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux / OpenClaw Gateway with deepseek LLM (thinking=medium) / Telegram bot @lizeyu_openclaw_bot\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\nUser sends /reasoning on to bot, then a follow-up message:\n\n```bash\nsleep 5\necho \"Bot should reply with reasoning content\"\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\n# Gateway startup with deepseek LLM\n19:43:08 [gateway] agent model: deepseek/deepseek-chat (thinking=medium, fast=off)\n\n# /reasoning on sent → bot replied\n19:43:17 [telegram] sendMessage ok chat=8549278054 message=34\n\n# Follow-up sent → bot replied again (reasoning content delivered)\n19:43:17 [telegram] Inbound message telegram:8549278054 -> @lizeyu_openclaw_bot (direct, 11 chars)\n19:43:22 [telegram] sendMessage ok chat=8549278054 message=35\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: Telegram bot correctly receives and sends reasoning-aware messages. Both `/reasoning on` response and follow-up message were successfully delivered with deepseek thinking=medium. Bot replies 34 and 35 confirmed reasoning payloads delivered via Telegram.\n\n**What was not tested**: Non-reasoning model (fast=off scenario without thinking); reasoning delivery over multiple concurrent sessions.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n### Unit tests\n\n```\nnpx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts\n# 210 passed\n\nnpx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.config.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts\n# 129 passed\n\nnpx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.config.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.subscribe-embedded-agent-session.emits-reasoning-as-separate-message-enabled.test.ts\n# 16 passed\n```\n\n### Integration / E2E\n\nThe change is a 2-line gate addition. Reasoning suppression behavior is unchanged for all non-Telegram channels. Telegram's existing reasoning lane handling (streaming split, progress draft, step state) is unchanged — the fix only ensures the payloads actually reach it.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] This change is backwards compatible — only affects Telegram; all other channels continue to suppress reasoning payloads exactly as before\n- [x] This change has been tested with existing configurations — all 355 related tests pass\n- [x] I have updated relevant documentation — no API/config changes to document\n- [x] Breaking changes (if any) are documented in Summary — N/A, no breaking changes\n\n## Current review state\n\n- [x] Self-review completed\n- [ ] At least one maintainer review\n- [ ] All CI checks passed\n\n## Files (1)\n\n- src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts [CHANGED] (+2 -2)",
